results.title: Wolverine Origins (2006) #44
results.description: SEVEN THE HARD WAY PART 4 Wolverine's plans have hit a snag. With Romulus breathing down his neck, Wolverine struggles to get his last piece on the board. And the fact that she's in prison doesn't exactly make it any easier...

results.title: Wolverine Origins (2006) #45
results.description: SEVEN THE HARD WAY CONCLUSION Wolverine's plan to take down Romulus is revealed, and the endgame to what it's all been building to begins! But who is the mastermind behind it all? And more importantly, will it even work?

results.title: Wolverine Origins (2006) #46
results.description: RECKONING PART 1 With his final confrontation with Romulus on the horizon, Wolverine reaches out to a friend to help him put to rest one of the greatest tragedies of his long, long life-the death of Mariko Yashida. Guest-starring Nightcrawler.

results.title: Wolverine Origins (2006) #47
results.description: RECKONING PART 2 As the pieces begin to move, Wolverine's plan begins to tear apart at the seams-has Skaar, the son of Hulk, become compromised by Romulus' influence? Will the reluctant Cloak be there when Wolverine needs him?

items.name: Wolverine Origins (2006) #47 (IRON MAN BY DESIGN VARIANT)

results.title: Wolverine Origins (2006) #48
results.description: RECKONING PART 3 Revenge. It is what has motivated Wolverine for over a century. But now, with that revenge within reach...is it really what he wants?

results.title: Wolverine Origins (2006) #49
results.description: His past finally behind him, Wolverine now turns to face another, more terrifying challenge: his future.

results.title: Wolverine Origins (2006) #50
results.description: THE SERIES CONCLUSION It's the end of an era, a story years in the making, and as one journey ends, another begins. With his quest for revenge now concluded, Wolverine embarks on a new journey...towards salvation.

results.description: The chronicle of the Marvel Universe returns as the All-New Official Index to the Marvel Universe delves into the history of three more of Marvelâ€™s most enduring titles! Return with us to the Silver and Golden Ages to we launch our coverage of the Avengers (from AVENGERS #345), Thor (from THOR #460), and Captain America (from both CAPTAIN AMERICA #387 and 1941â€™s CAPTAIN AMERICA COMICS #32). Watch the Marvel universeâ€™s history unfold month by month as each issue provides synopses for dozens of individual comics, including back-up strips, introducing the characters, teams, places and equipment that appeared within, providing vital information about first appearances, where they last showed up and where they appeared next!
